    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou2-vad-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment for COU2 (VAD hemolysis prediction, MRL 5, Class III) is accepted. Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall — Model Form at Gradation 3 against a required Gradation 4 — is addressed through conservative uncertainty bounds derived from multi-model comparison and is reflected in the Monte Carlo prediction intervals, which maintain 95th-percentile NIH predictions below the clinical threshold at all operating points. The assessment team judges that the aggregate evidence is sufficient to support the intended regulatory submission.",
